node.title: Thousands of protesters march through Melbourne as anti-lockdown, vaccine mandate rallies begin
node.alt: Protesters holding signs demonstrate in a city street
node.description: Crowds voicing anti-lockdown and anti-vaccine mandate messages have taken to the streets in Melbourne, Sydney and others parts of the country.
node.content:
["Thousands have gathered at rallies in Melbourne and Sydney today as part of an international day of protest against COVID-19 lockdowns and vaccine mandates.", "There was a large\u00a0police presence monitoring two separate crowds in Melbourne's CBD.", "Protesters had been camped outside Victoria's\u00a0Parliament House throughout the week calling for the scrapping of the state government's controversial pandemic bill.", "Today thousands more have joined\u00a0and have begun marching through the city.", "Meanwhile, another group of protesters, who\u00a0have labelled themselves anti-fascist, gathered for a\u00a0rally at the Eight Hour Day\u00a0Monument in Russell Street.", "Police have cordoned off the area, separating the two groups.", "Thousands of protesters\u00a0have also gathered in Sydney and across other parts of the country.", "", "
Hundreds were gathered in Sydney.(AAP: Steven Saphore)
", "More to come."]
